The code you provided is almost correct. However, it is missing the declaration of the `range` variable. To ensure this code works correctly, add the `let` keyword before the `range` variable declaration:

```javascript
function generateRange(min, max, step) {
  let range = [];
  for (let i = min; i <= max; i = i + step) {
    range.push(i);
  }
  return range;
}
```

With this correction, the code will create a `range` array and populate it with numbers starting from `min` and incrementing by `step` until reaching or exceeding `max`. Finally, the function will return the generated range as an array.

To remove the spaces between numbers in the result of the code you provided, you can modify the `range.push(i)` line to convert the `i` value to a string and remove any spaces using the `replace()` method:

```javascript
function generateRange(min, max, step) {
  let range = [];
  for (let i = min; i <= max; i = i + step) {
    range.push(i.toString().replace(/\s/g, ''));
  }
  return range;
}
```

In this code, I added `toString()` to convert the number `i` to a string. Then, the `replace()` method uses a regular expression (`/\s/g`) with the global flag `g` to match all spaces and replace them with an empty string `''`. This removes any spaces present in the resulting strings.

Now, when you call the `generateRange()` function, it will return an array with numbers where any spaces have been removed.

